						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Slab lying in the old village site on the bank of the Bhīmarathi.</hi></p>						

						<p>Siṅghaṇa—(Undated).</p>						

						<p>The inscription records a gift of some land made to the temple of Chandēśvaradēva at <hi rend="bold">Taddavāḍige,</hi> by <hi rend="bold">Chandarasa,</hi> the <hi rend="italic">manneya</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Taddavāḍi-nāḍu,</hi> on the occasion of a total solar eclipse <hi rend="italic">(kattaleya-grahaṇa).</hi> The gift was entrusted to Bijja-jīya, the <hi rend="italic">āchārya</hi> of the temple of Sōmanāthadēva at <hi rend="bold">Ṭakkaḷige.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
